# Dynamic Box UI Application

**Tech Stack:** JavaScript, DOM Manipulation, HTML, CSS

## Overview
An interactive UI application that allows users to dynamically create, modify, style, and remove visual components on the page using vanilla JavaScript.

## Key Features
- Dynamic creation and removal of DOM elements
- Real-time style updates and rendering
- Event handling for clicks, hovers, keyboard, and mouse input
- Scalable UI logic using state variables

## Technical Highlights
- Event delegation for performance and scalability
- Modular helper functions for rendering and updates
- Clear separation of state and UI logic

## Skills Demonstrated
- DOM traversal and manipulation
- State management patterns
- Event-driven programming
- Component-style architecture without frameworks

## How to Run
1. Clone the repository
2. Open `index.html` in your browser

---
Demonstrates mastery of vanilla JavaScript and UI architecture fundamentals.
